Manasseh, and all the land of Judah, unto the utmost sea,","year":-1451},{"id":"recGUKDxNmib03LE2","ref":"Deut.34.3","text":"And the south, and the plain of the valley of Jericho, the city of palm trees, unto Zoar.","year":-1451},{"id":"recfJRFadgMjovTna","ref":"Deut.34.4","text":"And the LORD said unto him, This is the land which I sware unto Abraham, unto Isaac, and unto Jacob, saying, I will give it unto thy seed: I have caused thee to see it with thine eyes, but thou shalt not go over thither.","year":-1451},{"id":"recP1stLoJ2sVw4zT","ref":"Deut.34.5","text":"So Moses the servant of the LORD died there in the land of Moab, according to the word of the LORD.","year":-1451},{"id":"recmcjyXdfbhRsnPv","ref":"Deut.34.6","text":"And he buried him in a valley in the land of Moab, over against Bethpeor: but no man knoweth of his sepulchre unto this day.","year":-1451},{"id":"rec7JrLIRYdCDEZtl","ref":"Deut.34.7","text":"And Moses was an hundred and twenty years old when he died: his eye was not dim, nor his natural force abated.","year":-1451},{"id":"recb02HNzCylqIksi","ref":"Deut.34.8","text":"And the children of Israel wept for Moses in the plains of Moab thirty days: so the days of weeping and mourning for Moses were ended.","year":-1451}]}
